From: Sai Lakshmi Teja Vanka <SaiLakshmiTeja.Vanka@windriver.com>
Date: Wed, 20 May 2026 10:53:00 -0400
Subject: Switch gunicorn worker from eventlet to gthread

eventlet 0.40.3 (Trixie) introduced _green_existing_locks() in
monkey_patch() which triggers a Django lazy import chain during worker
init. The chain spawns /sbin/ldconfig via ctypes.util.find_library(),
and the resulting SIGCHLD crashes the eventlet hub with:
  RuntimeError: do not call blocking functions from the mainloop

Switch from eventlet to gthread workers with 4 threads per worker.
Horizon code has no dependency on eventlet monkey-patching. gthread
provides adequate concurrency via native Python threads without the
eventlet/SIGCHLD interaction.

Signed-off-by: Sai Lakshmi Teja Vanka <SaiLakshmiTeja.Vanka@windriver.com>
---
 horizon.init | 5 +++--
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/horizon.init b/horizon.init
index 1c05e5a..8478e18 100755
--- a/horizon.init
+++ b/horizon.init
@@ -21,7 +21,8 @@ MANAGE="/usr/share/openstack-dashboard/manage.py"
 EXEC="/usr/bin/gunicorn"
 BIND="localhost"
 PORT="8008"
-WORKER="eventlet"
+WORKER="gthread"
+THREADS="4"
 WORKERS=`grep workers /etc/openstack-dashboard/horizon-config.ini | cut -f3 -d' '`
 # Increased timeout to facilitate large image uploads
 TIMEOUT="200"
@@ -71,7 +72,7 @@ start()
         -p Description="${SERVICE_DESC}" \
         -p CPUShares=${SERVICE_CPUSHARES} -p PIDFile=${PIDFILE} \
         ${EXEC} --pid ${PIDFILE} --preload --bind ${BIND}:${PORT} \
-        --worker-class ${WORKER} --workers ${WORKERS} --timeout ${TIMEOUT} \
+        --worker-class ${WORKER} --workers ${WORKERS} --threads ${THREADS} --timeout ${TIMEOUT} \
         --log-syslog  \
         --config '/usr/share/openstack-dashboard/guni_config.py' \
         --pythonpath '/usr/share/openstack-dashboard' \
